metadata.name: I Fear No Fire - Hanuman
metadata.description:
This photograph is a frame of a scene from Ramayana enacted by Kecak Dance performers of Uluwatu Temple, Bali, Indonesia. Hanuman is in the frame, fearless!

Hanuman is a fearless monkey God in Lord Rama's army. The scene is set where Lord Rama's wife, Sita mata, is abducted by Ravana, the demon king of Lanka.
Upon Lord Rama's directions, Hanuman flies to Sri Lanka from India to inform Sita mata that Lord Rama is on his way with a vast army to liberate her from the evil clutches of Ravana.

While in Lanka, Hanuman is captured for interrogation. Hanuman being a fearless warrior sets the courthouse of Lanka on fire with his tail.

The Kecak performers have beautifully enacted this story. I took this photo during the climax scene of the act.

Details:
Camera: Nikon D5600
Dimensions: 6000 x 4000
762 dpi
ISO: 800
F-stop: f/5.6

The collector of this NFT will get an HQ version of this photograph.
